    public class REMImpl
extends REMAbstract
implements net.hudup.core.alg.DuplicatableAlg
    This class implements default expectation maximization algorithm for regression model in case of missing data, called REM algorithm REM. Exactly, it is default implementation of REM algorithm REM.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • data

        protected LargeStatistics data
        Internal data is the original data for learning. It can have missing values.

      • xIndices

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Object[]> xIndices
        Indices for X data. Each element of xIndixes is an index which is an array of objects. In current implementation, only the first object of the array is used. Such first object can be number, variable name (field name), or mathematical expression. If it is a number called number index, the 0 index always points to 1 and the 1 index points the first field (index 0) of profile. In other words, number index starts with 1 when users specify.

      • zIndices

        protected java.util.List<java.lang.Object[]> zIndices
        Indices for Z data. Each element of zIndices is an index which is an array of objects. Note, xIndices has only two indices. In current implementation, only the first object of the array is used. Such first object can be number, variable name (field name), or mathematical expression. If it is a number called number index, the 0 index always points to 1 and the 1 index points the first field (index 0) of profile. In other words, number index starts with 1 when users specify.

      • attList

        protected net.hudup.core.data.AttributeList attList
        Attribute list for all variables: all X, Y, and z. This variable is also used as the indicator of successful learning (not null).

      • estimateInverse

        @Deprecated
protected Statistics estimateInverse(Statistics stat,
                                                  java.util.List<java.lang.Double> alpha,
                                                  java.util.List<double[]> betas)
        Deprecated. 
        Estimating statistics with specified parameters alpha and beta. This method does not change internal data. Balance process is removed because it is over-fitting or not stable. Balance process is the best in some cases. This method is as good as than estimate(Statistics, List, List) method but it is not stable for long regression model having many regressors because solving a set of many equations can cause approximate solution or non-solution problem.
        Parameters:
        stat - specified statistics.
        alpha - specified alpha parameter.
        betas - specified alpha parameters.
        Returns:
        estimated statistics with specified parameters alpha and beta. Return null if any error raises.
